properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 11 at 5:14PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
Lake-effect snow showers will continue this evening for parts of
the South Shore and the southwestern tip of Lake Superior,
including northern Ashland county and the Bayfield Peninsula, west
to include the Twin Ports and Carlton county area, and then up the
North Shore to the Two Harbors and Silver Bay areas.

If you will be out driving this evening, be prepared for rapidly
changing visibilities and road conditions. Due to the localized
nature of lake-effect snow, snow accumulations will vary across
short distances. Up to 2 inches of snow may fall locally under the
heaviest bands this evening.

NWSheadline: LAKE-EFFECT SNOW SHOWERS TO CONTINUE THIS EVENING
